  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "I am trying out `kubectl port-forward` and I think it does not close the client-side connection properly when the server closes the connection.\n\nI realize this example is probably deeply unhelpful unless you have a zookeeper image lying around, but here's what I observed...\n\nWhen I ssh in to the minion and target the pod IP, I send the \"status\" message (ruok) and the server sends the reply (imok) and closes the connection.\n\n```\njustinsb@kubernetes-minion-nyy1:~$ echo ruok | nc 10.244.1.5 2181\nimok\njustinsb@kubernetes-minion-nyy1:~$\n```\n\nBut when I try to do this on the client:\n\n```\n kubectl port-forward -p zookeeper-rplo3 2181 \n```\n\nand then\n\n```\necho ruok | nc 127.0.0.1 2181\nimok\n<hangs>\n```\n\nI hope to publish this zookeeper image early this week, if you can't find another test-image where the server closes the connection.\n",
